# InterGenOS Credits and Attribution

InterGenOS is built on the work of many open source projects and communities.
We are grateful for their contributions and committed to proper attribution.

## Linux From Scratch (LFS)

InterGenOS core is built following the Linux From Scratch 13.0 methodology.

    LFS 13.0 (systemd edition)
    Copyright (C) 1999-2026 Gerard Beekmans et al.
    Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 2.0
    https://www.linuxfromscratch.org/lfs/

LFS provides the foundational build methodology, package selection, and
configuration guidance that InterGenOS core follows. Our core tier (Ch 5-10)
adheres closely to LFS 13.0 with documented deviations.

## Beyond Linux From Scratch (BLFS)

InterGenOS desktop and extended packages follow BLFS 13.0 guidance.

    BLFS 13.0 (systemd edition)
    Copyright (C) 1999-2026 The BLFS Development Team
    Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 2.0
    https://www.linuxfromscratch.org/blfs/

BLFS provides build instructions, dependency information, and configuration
guidance for packages beyond the base LFS system. Our desktop tier follows
BLFS 13.0 with documented deviations.

## LFS/BLFS Patches

The build/patches/ directory contains patches distributed by the LFS and
BLFS projects for fixing build issues and security vulnerabilities.

    LFS/BLFS Patches
    https://www.linuxfromscratch.org/patches/
    Distributed under the same license as the respective packages they modify.

## Individual Package Authors

Every package built by InterGenOS is the work of its respective authors and
communities. See individual package licenses in packages/*/package.yml.

